      • mainMenu

        public void mainMenu()
        This method prints the main interface of the app, and opens sub-interfaces based on a number given by the user. Loops until the user stop it.
        Pre: A Menu object is instantiated.
        Post: The interface was printed.

      • creationMenu

        public int creationMenu(int angelNumber)
        This method prints and reads the requirements for the creation of an archangel. It checks every requirement submitted in search of any error, and then adds 1 to the archangel counter.
        Post: The requirements were printed and loaded. Archangel counter is raised by 1. The requirements were printed, but in the load, one was invalid. Archangel counter stays the same.
        Parameters:
        angelNumber. - Archangel counter.
        Returns:
        angelNumber raised by 1. Same angelNumber (in case of an error).

      • searchMenu

        public void searchMenu()
        This method prints and reads the conditions for printing the details of an archangel.
        Post: The name/power was loaded and the details were printed. The name/power was loaded but an error is printed.

      • datesMenu

        public void datesMenu()
        This method prints the options of searching dates, reads an integer given by the user, and if the integer is 1, it also reads a month given by the user.
        Post: The dates were printed. An error message is printed.

      • init

        public void init()
        This method loads default archangels in a legion.
        Post: The archangels are loaded.
